verses.text:
On Jor-dan's stor-my banks I stand, And cast a wish-ful eye
To Ca-naan's fair and hap-py land, Where my pos-ses-sions lie;
I will with-draw my ran-somed soul Want from a sin-ful stay.

There gen-erous fruits that nev-er fail On trees im-mor-tal grow;
There rocks and hills and brooks and vales With milk and hon-ey flow.
When shall I reach that hap-py place, And be for-ev-er blest?

All o'er those wide ex-tend-ed plains Shines one e-ter-nal day;
There God the Son for-ev-er reigns, And scat-ters night a-way.
When shall I reach that hap-py place, And be for-ev-er blest?
